quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  24,11,"Those who have brought up such slander from a clique among you. Do not think it is a bad thing for you; rather it will be good for you: every last man of them shall be charged with whatever he has committed the way of an offence, while whoever has assumed his leadership over them [through such gossiping] will have serious torment."
  24,12,"If you believing men and believing women had only thought of something good by yourselves when you heard it, and said: "This is an obvious falsehood!""
  24,13,"If they had only brought four witnesses to [prove] it! When they did not bring any witnesses, those were liars before Allah (God)."
  24,14,"If it had not been for Allah (God)'s bounty towards you, as well as His mercy in this world and the Hereafter, some serious torment might have afflicted you because of the talk you had indulged in."
  24,15,"When you encountered it on your tongues and said something with your own mouths that you had no knowledge about, you thought it was trifling although it was serious with Allah (God)."
  24,16,"If you had only said as you heard it: "We ought not to talk about this. Glory be to You! This is serious slander.""
  24,17,"Allah (God) cautions you never to repeat anything like it again if you are believers."
  24,18,"Allah (God) explains signs to you; Allah (God) is All-Knowing, Wise."
  24,19,"Those who love to spread immorality [news] around concerning those who believe will have painful torment in this world and the Hereafter. Allah (God) knows while you (all) do not know."
  24,20,"If Allah (God)'s bounty and mercy had only rested on you; for Allah (God) is Gentle, Merciful!"